original: Jansson, Johian Bertil, kyrkoherde, Rörviik, f. 18/7/07 i Lekaryd, Kronob. 1., av Carl J. o. Gertnud Johansson;. G. 37 m. Edit Thuné. Barn: Anna-Karin f. 39, Anders 41. — Stud:-ex. i Lund 27, teol. fil. ex. där 29, teol. kand., prakt. ’teol. prov ’samt prästvigd f. Växjö stift 34. Tjg. s. past:-adj. i Kalvsvik o. Södra Hestra samt s. v. kommin. i Oskarshamn, kommin. i Södra Sol ber ga 38, i Haimmeda 40, kyrkoh. i Hjälmseryd 47.
translated: Jansson, Johian Bertil, church pastor, Rörvik, born July 18, 1907 in Lekaryd, Kronoburg County. Son of Carl J. and Gertnud Johansson. Married in 1937 to Edit Thuné and had two children: Anna-Karin born in 1939 and Anders born in 1941. He graduated from Lund University with a degree in Theology in 1927, followed by a degree in Philosophy in 1929. He passed his practical theology exam and was ordained as a priest for Växjö Diocese in 1934. He served as a deputy pastor in Kalvsvik and Södra Hestra, and then as a curate in Oskarshamn. He became a curate in Södra Solberga in 1938, in Haimmeda in 1940, and finally a church pastor in Hjälmseryd in 1947.
